HEADWORD: Thecophora
<hw>The*coph"o*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <?/ a case + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of hydroids comprising those which
have the hydranths in thecae and the gonophores in capsules. The
campanularians and sertularians are examples. Called also
<altname>Thecata</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Hydroidea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thecosomata</ent>⟦br⟧
